    <title type="text">Oddities and Curious Lands</title>
    <id>http://andmeyer.com/2012/07/24/arcticacre-oddities</id>
    <updated>2012-07-24T00:00:00Z</updated>
    <link href="http://andmeyer.com/2012/07/24/arcticacre-oddities" />
    <author>
      <name>Eric A. Meyer</name>
    </author>
    <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;In case you are ever bored,
there are some things you should be doing
on the internet.
Several of those things were made by
&lt;a class="reference external" href="http://www.secrettechnology.com/"&gt;Jason Nelson&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;figure&gt;
  &lt;a href="http://www.arcticacre.com/"&gt;
    &lt;img src="/static/pictures/i-made-this.jpg" alt="ArcticAcre Oddities and Curious Lands" /&gt;
  &lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;figcaption&gt;
    The &lt;a href="http://www.arcticacre.com/"&gt;arctic(acre) is not&lt;/a&gt;
    to say cold,
    so much as barren,
    unable to procreate in the usual sense,
    and so making what the he in question calls games
    or poetry or chaos
    or any other
    &lt;a href="http://lmgtfy.com/?q=ramblemancy"&gt;ramblemancy&lt;/a&gt;
    of words like butter.
    Birthed by the maternal
    womb-like structures of Adobe Flash,
    and his fear of obsolesence.
  &lt;/figcaption&gt;
&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You might start with the &lt;a class="reference external" href="http://www.arcticacre.com/"&gt;games&lt;/a&gt;
(&amp;quot;i made this, you play this, we are enemies&amp;quot;
shown above),
then perhaps some
&amp;quot;&lt;a class="reference external" href="http://www.secrettechnology.com/songs/harmsong1.html"&gt;Stunningly Harmful Songs&lt;/a&gt;...for
spreading and baffling and loving.&amp;quot;
You can explore on your own from there.&lt;/p&gt;
</content>
